   "source": [
    "## Data Generation Process\n",
    "\n",
    "**Structural Equation Model**: Following the lab convention where each causal arrow represents a unit effect, we implement the structural equations:\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Z₃ = ε_{Z₃}** (exogenous variable)\n",
    "2. **Z₁ = ε_{Z₁}** (exogenous variable)  \n",
    "3. **Z₂ = Z₃ + ε_{Z₂}** (Z₃ affects Z₂ with coefficient 1)\n",
    "4. **X = Z₁ + Z₂ + ε_X** (both confounders affect treatment)\n",
    "5. **Y = X + Z₁ + Z₂ + Z₃ + ε_Y** (true causal effect is 1)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Key Parameters**:\n",
    "- **True causal effect**: β_{X→Y} = 1 (this is what we want to estimate)\n",
    "- **Confounding effects**: Z₁ and Z₂ each contribute 1 unit to both X and Y\n",
    "- **Upstream effect**: Z₃ contributes 1 unit to Y directly and 1 unit through Z₂\n",
    "- **Error terms**: εᵢ ~ N(0,1) for all variables\n",
    "\n",
    "**Sample Size**: N = 10,000 for sufficient power to detect bias and distinguish between models\""
   ]
  },
